data.title: JOHN WILLIAM STRUTT SIGNED CARD, 1904 NOBEL PRIZE PHYSICS, OPTICS, ACOUSTICS
data.meta_description: He receivedthe 1904 Nobel Prize in Physics for his investigations of the densities of the most important gases and for his discovery of argon in connection with these studies. He was president of the Royal Society (1905-8), spent his academic career at the University of Cambridge and was Chancellor (1908-19).
